					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, a big part of them and the most complexes ones. The only part remaining is the intermediate code to target assembly code translation, which also need optimizations in the process (as register allocation..) but it's much more simpler that handling a complete compiler from scratch <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />Here you have a nice tutorial about compiler design :<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.tutorialspoint.com/compiler_design/index.htm">https://www.tutorialspoint.com/compiler ... /index.htm</a><!-- m --><br />You can see how far is the intermediate code generation in the process, it's why it's interesting to only consider that last step of intermediate code to target code translation if possible.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

